# ESP32-C3-Motor

RISC-V motor and actuator controller. Manages motor PWM via LEDC, WiFi TX sweep for channel selection, and NVS-backed crash logging with brownout recovery.

## Source Files

| File | Description |
|:-----|:------------|
| `main.c` | Application entry point |
| `motor_control.c` | Motor PWM control via LEDC |
| `wifi_tx_sweep.c` / `wifi_tx_sweep.h` | WiFi channel TX sweep |
| `crash_log.c` / `crash_log.h` | NVS-backed crash logging |
| `network_config.h` | Network configuration |
| `wifi_secrets.h` | WiFi credentials (not committed) |

## Build Profiles

Two sdkconfig profiles are provided — use `sdkconfig.usb` for bench/debug, `sdkconfig.uart` for battery deployment.

### Environment Setup

```bash
cd esp32-c3-motor
. $HOME/esp/esp-idf/export.sh

# Clean (avoid cache issues)
idf.py -C ~/embedded-iot-hub/esp32-c3-motor \
  -B ~/embedded-iot-hub/esp32-c3-motor/build \
  fullclean
```

### Bench USB — log + reset

```bash
cp sdkconfig.usb sdkconfig
idf.py -C ~/embedded-iot-hub/esp32-c3-motor/ build
```

### Bench USB — halt on crash (JTAG attached)

```bash
cp sdkconfig.usb sdkconfig
idf.py -C ~/embedded-iot-hub/esp32-c3-motor/ build -DCRASH_HALT=1
```

### Battery deployment — UART console

```bash
cp sdkconfig.uart sdkconfig
idf.py -C ~/embedded-iot-hub/esp32-c3-motor/ build
```

## Flash

```bash
idf.py -C ~/embedded-iot-hub/esp32-c3-motor \
  -B ~/embedded-iot-hub/esp32-c3-motor/build \
  -p /dev/ttyUSB0 flash
```

## Monitor

```bash
minicom -D /dev/ttyUSB0 -b 115200
```

## Crash Logging

`CRASH_HALT` controls panic handler behavior:
- `0` — log PC to NVS and restart (default, release/battery)
- `1` — halt forever for JTAG debugger

Toggle at build time with `-DCRASH_HALT=1` — no source changes needed.
